-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                             ==== INSTALL ====

                              -- BLACKFISK --
                            Version 0.0.0 alpha
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

There is no need for a install routine. Just unpack all files to a directory
and start the binary (blackfisk.exe on windows).
On first start Blackfisk will create a configuration file "blackfisk.cfg" and
a log file "bf.log".
That is all!

Please feel free to contact me if you need more informations!

FILE & DIRECTORY LISTING
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 README         - general informations
 INSTALL        - installation instructions (this file)
 LICENSE        - license information
 HISTORY        - history of blackfisk development
 CREDITS        - all persons, projects and institutions
                  related to this project
 CHANGELOG      - differences between the blackfisk versions
 blackfisk.exe  - the windows (32bit) binary
 graphic/       - icons and other graphic stuff for blackfisk
 local/         - language files (*.mo) for blackfisk
 sound/         - sound files for event-notification

 -- (extra files and directories in the source package) --
 build/					- build environment
 build/README			- informations how to build blackfisk
 build/BF.workspace		- workspace file for the IDE Code::Blocks
 build/blackfisk.cbp	- project file for the IDE Code::Blocks
 build/blackfisk.sln	- Microsoft Visual C++ Express Edition Solution file
 build/blackfisk.vcproj	- Microsoft Visual C++ Express Edition Project file
 include/				- header files
 src/					- source files
 graphic/src			- SVG source files for graphic stuff
 third-party/			- 3rd-party components like wxSerialize
						  Please see the doc-files in the related directory
						  for more detailes.
 local/*.po				- GNU gettext based language files (*.po)
 TODO					- This is just a little TODO list for blackfisk.
						  Please use the bugtracking-system on BerliOS instead
						  of this file.
